HEADWORD: Clonic
<hw>Clon"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>klo`nos</grk> a violent, confused motion; cf. F.
<ets>clonique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Having an irregular,
convulsive motion.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Clonic spasm</b></col>. <fld>(Med.)</fld> <cd>See under
